## Tech Stack Decision

The full rationale is at `context/foundation/tech-stack.md`. Reference it with `@context/foundation/tech-stack.md` when you need the complete document.

### Key Facts

- Starter: T3 (Next.js 15 + tRPC + Drizzle + Tailwind)
- Auth: Neon Auth (co-located with DB, no separate auth service)
- Deploy: Vercel (native Next.js target)
- CI: GitHub Actions, auto-deploy-on-merge
- Package manager: pnpm (strict isolated)
- Language: TypeScript (strict mode)

### When to Load Full Doc

- Evaluating a new dependency — check if it aligns with stack rationale
- Changing auth flow — Neon Auth integration details are documented there
- Modifying CI/CD — deployment target and CI shape decisions are there
- Questioning "why this stack" — the four agent-friendly quality gates and selection rationale
